    "creation_date" : 1307099302,
    "answer_id" : 6226322,
    "question_id" : 6226290,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The default value of any <code>Object</code>, such as <code>Boolean</code>, is <code>null</code>.</p>\n\n<p>The default value for a <code>boolean</code> is false.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Every primitive has a wrapper class. Every wrapper uses a reference which has a default of <code>null</code>. Primitives have different default values:</p>\n\n<pre><code>boolean -&gt; false\n\nbyte, char, short, int, long -&gt; 0\n\nfloat, double -&gt; 0.0\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><strong>Note (2):</strong> <code>void</code> has a wrapper <code>Void</code> which also has a default of <code>null</code> and is it's only possible value (without using hacks).</p>\n"
  }, {
